OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1779951883
OL,3,CHow to stay safe in the water during
OL,4,Cwarm weather
OL,6,FWhat makes the water dangerous this
OL,7,Ftime of year?
OL,9,FThe warm weather over the Bank Holiday
OL,10,Fweekend drew many people to beaches,
OL,11,Frivers and lakes, but Tipton described
OL,12,Fit as "the most dangerous part of the
OL,13,Fyear".
OL,15,FThe danger comes from cold shock,
OL,16,Fwhich happens when someone suddenly
OL,17,Fenters water colder than 15C and the
OL,18,Fbody reacts unexpectedly to the rapid
OL,19,Fdrop in temperature.
OL,26,@tD@GOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1779951883
OL,3,CHow to stay safe in the water during
OL,4,Cwarm weather
OL,6,FThe RNLI says water below 15C is
OL,7,Fconsidered cold and can seriously
OL,8,Faffect breathing and movement,
OL,9,Fincreasing the risk of drowning.
OL,11,FAverage sea temperatures around the UK
OL,12,Fand Ireland are about 12C, while
OL,13,Frivers such as the Thames can be even
OL,14,Fcolder, including during summer.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
