OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1779951883
OL,3,CHow to stay safe in the water during
OL,4,Cwarm weather
OL,6,FProfessor Tipton said: "People look to
OL,7,Fcool off by going into the water. The
OL,8,Fproblem is the air temperature shoots
OL,9,Fup very quickly. It's very easy to
OL,10,Fheat air, but the water temperature
OL,11,Ftakes much longer. In fact, it doesn't
OL,12,Freach its peak until about September.
OL,14,F"So we've got people now who are
OL,15,Fgetting very hot and charging into
OL,16,Fwater that's still around winter
OL,17,Ftemperatures.
OL,26,@nD@XOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1779951883
OL,3,CHow to stay safe in the water during
OL,4,Cwarm weather
OL,6,F"So it's about 13C, and in those
OL,7,Ftemperatures you get very significant
OL,8,Fphysiological responses, particularly
OL,9,Fthe cold shock response, which is a
OL,10,Fgasp and uncontrollable
OL,11,Fhyperventilation, which is often a
OL,12,Fprecursor to drowning.
OL,14,F"About 60% of those that die going
OL,15,Finto cold water do so in the first
OL,16,Fminute or so of immersion."
OL,18,FWhat happens to the body during cold
OL,19,Fwater shock?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1779951883
OL,3,CHow to stay safe in the water during
OL,4,Cwarm weather
OL,6,FThe RNLI says cold water shock causes
OL,7,Fblood vessels in the skin to narrow,
OL,8,Fincreasing resistance to blood flow.
OL,10,FThis raises your heart rate and blood
OL,11,Fpressure, forcing the heart to work
OL,12,Fharder.
OL,14,FIn some cases, the sudden strain can
OL,15,Ftrigger a heart attack, even in people
OL,16,Fwho are young and healthy
OL,18,FSudden exposure to cold water can also
OL,19,Ftrigger involuntary gasps for breath.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
