PN,31608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1779951883
OL,3,CHow to stay safe in the water during
OL,4,Cwarm weather
OL,6,FBreathing can become rapid and
OL,7,Funcontrollable, sometimes increasing
OL,8,Fup to tenfold, which can cause panic
OL,9,Fand increase the risk of inhaling
OL,10,Fwater into the lungs.
OL,12,FThe RNLI warns this can happen very
OL,13,Fquickly, adding that it takes only
OL,14,Faround half a pint of seawater
OL,15,Fentering the lungs for an adult to
OL,16,Fbegin drowning.
OL,18,FWithout immediate medical treatment,
OL,19,Fcold water shock can lead to death.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
