OL,3,CHow to stay safe in the water during
OL,4,Cwarm weather
OL,6,FHow to deal with cold water shock and
OL,7,Freduce the risk?
OL,9,FProfessor Tipton advises that the most
OL,10,Fimportant step is to think before
OL,11,Fentering cold water, rather than
OL,12,Fjumping in unexpectedly.
OL,14,FIf you do find yourself in trouble,
OL,15,Fthe advice is to "Float to Live", roll
OL,16,Fonto your back, keep your head back,
OL,17,Fears in the water and airway clear,
OL,18,Fand do as little as possible until
OL,19,Fyour breathing returns to normal.
OL,26,@wD@ROUwD@`O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
